# Secret-handling preference: AVOID putting secrets on disk where you can.
# In order of preference:
#   1. Shell export (ephemeral, never on disk):  export RAPIDAPI_KEY=...
#   2. A secret manager via *_CMD (key stays in the manager, not in a file):
#        export RAPIDAPI_KEY_CMD="op read op://Private/rapidapi/key"
#        export RAPIDAPI_KEY_CMD="pass show rapidapi/key"
#   3. This .env file — convenience fallback only (gitignored, but still on disk).
#
# Copy this file to `.env` only if you choose option 3. `.env.example` is
# committed; `.env` is NOT. The loader prefers 1 and 2 over `.env`.

# RapidAPI key — a single key works across every API on your RapidAPI account.
# Used by the UAE Real Estate API (host uae-real-estate3.p.rapidapi.com), which
# serves DLD transactions + Ejari rents. Subscribe to the Basic (free) plan first.
RAPIDAPI_KEY=

# Optional: the listings client (src/dddxb/ingest/bayut.py) reads this; it falls
# back to RAPIDAPI_KEY if unset, so you usually don't need it separately.
# BAYUT_API_KEY=

# --- Dubai Pulse open-data API (only if you ever go that route) ---
# DUBAI_PULSE_API_KEY=
# DUBAI_PULSE_API_SECRET=

# --- UAE residential proxy for the keyless Dubai Pulse CSV route (optional) ---
# DDDXB_PROXY=http://user:pass@host:port
